<br>
As the sun started to peek over the flat lands, wafting its rays of sunlight over the grasses and sparse trees of the Karana Plains, the wood elf woman unwraps the package to reveal a young strong sprig of a hardy oak tree, a mere stick compared to the great trees of Kelethin, but one filled with promise, memories ... and more ...<br>
<br>
It took days and weeks to prepare the little sprig ... days of prayer from both Priests of Tunare and Karana ... days of prayer by a certain wood elf whose thoughts were of nothing but memories of another half elf.  The sapling's wood practically glowed with its imbued magics ... magics to ensure the sapling will grow even in the plains, even under the Plaguebringer's curse ...<br>
<br>
A hole is carefully dug by small hands holding a hardened wooden spade, for no metal must profane the ground.  Rough handwoven cloth is unwrapped gently from the roots and placed aside as the sapling is settled into its new home ... rich dirt is moved back into place about the roots, giving solid anchor for the sapling to resist the winds that will come ...<br>
<br>
The Sapling now in place, the small figure sits back upon her heels, head bowed in prayer ...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Blessed Tunare, Mother to Nature all ... Strong Karana, Father of the Storms ... this is my legacy in memory of a beloved husband never forgotten ... treat this Sapling well, make it grow, make it strong, make it forever live with all the memories of one who loved him deeply ...&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
A catch in the winsome woodelf's throat forces a pause, a tear threads it's way down smooth browned cheek, leaving a wet track of sorrow felt, love lost, memories powerful.<br>
<br>
With a difficult swallow, she presses on as the sun lights the land fully ...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Make it Live.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
As if heard by said Deities, a few splatters of rain start to fall, making little indentations upon the newly turned earth which drinks thirstily.  As the rain slowly builds, the faemaiden stands, pale blue eyes filled with emotions matching the weather.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;I miss you Triam.  May you forever live with Karana.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The rain pours down ...<br>
